text: Frank Durand (March 9, 1895 – June 15, 1978) was an American politician who served in the New Jersey General Assembly from 1930 to 1931 and in the New Jersey Senate from 1933 to 1938. ==References== Category:1895 births Category:1978 deaths Category:Majority Leaders of the New Jersey Senate Category:Members of the New Jersey General Assembly Category:New Jersey Republicans Category:New Jersey state senators Category:People from Asbury Park, New Jersey Category:Presidents of the New Jersey Senate
title: Frank Durand
